parameters: This switch has no lever.\.\. You can't turn it on like this...
\n<\n[3]>The Lake Goddess Shrine...\.\.\. I doubt it,\. but are you religious,\. Neneko?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Nah.\.\. I don't need a goddess to do things for me.\.\. I make my own way.\.\. The only girl I rely on is me.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>A rather direct viewpoint...\.\.\. I don't know if that is respectable or not.\.\.

\n<\n[3]>Sigh...\.\.\. either way,\. I suppose you won't have any problem going inside,\. then.\.\. \BST[1]Hopefully your attitude won't anger the goddess and deprive the city and the Hole of its clean water.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Ehh,\. you're talking like it's a death trap or something.\.\. I dunno anything about angering goddesses,\. but it wasn't so bad last time I went in.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>You...\.\.\. already went into the temple on your own?\.\. But why?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>I unno.\.\. Figured there might be something down there with all the rumors.\.\. It wasn't all that tough,\. though~\.\.
\n<\n[3]>You really...\.\.\. but all those rumors?\.\. The monsters...!\.\. And all the mechanisms to keep people out...\.\.\. Did you...\.\.\. was the Kirin in there?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Eh...\.\.\. There was a big thing that was probably a Kirin?\.\. Way too heavy for me to carry out and I didn't feel like cutting it up for parts,\. though...\.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>You've really exceeded all of my expectations of you,\. but if you are telling the truth,\. that makes all of this much easier.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>No one ever enters this place because of the monsters.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Normally that would be a problem,\. but if you've already conquered the temple,\. that means it's likely the Kirin's body is still down below.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>You just need to go back down \c[18]and harvest its \ii[22]\c[0].\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Heh~\.\. I do like it when things are easy~\.\. Guess my instincts paid off again~\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Nyahaha~\.\. Hey,\. maybe it was your Lake Goddess that made me go in there before,\. huh?~\.\.
\n<\n[3]>...\.\.\.I'm not sure I like you being smug.\.\. Sigh.\.\. Please don't invoke the Goddess' wrath while we're right outside of her shrine.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Just gotta make my way down again...\.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>You kept me waiting.\.\. For the one who is on this quest you seem to enjoy wasting time.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Tch...!\.\. You've got a lotta bite all of a sudden,\. huh!?\.\. What's wrong with you?!\.\.
\n<\n[3]>...\.\.\. I wanted to speak to you in private about this errand,\. that is all.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>...\.\.\.I believe we should change our plans.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>I wished to get Anemone to help us,\. but something wasn't...\.\.\. right about her.\.\. \BST[6]She was acting strange,\. particularly around you.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>I have never seen her behave like that,\. and I got a strange,\. suspicious feeling from her,\. as well...\.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>I believe she has something else planned,\. and I don't think it is anything good.\.\. We cannot help her.\.\. I doubt even going back to her will be safe.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Ehh...?\.\. What're you even talking about?\.\. \BST[8]So,\. what,\. you don't trust her?\.\.

\n<\n[1]>Well that's just great!\.\. So what,\. we're here for nothing!?\.\. Hey,\. what were you saying about wasting time?\.\. Cuz to me it looks like your little "plan" was the waste of time here!\.\.
Neneko growls,\. approaching Kaere.\.\. The witch is unphased.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Enough,\. you impatient cat.\.\. Our partnership is still on.\.\. I said I wished to change the plan,\. not throw it away.\.\.
Neneko glares.\.\. Kaere raises her hands placatingly,\. urging her to listen.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Ane might not be our answer,\. but coming here could still bear fruit,\. if her report of a Kirin claiming the shrine is accurate.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>So we're still on a Kirin hunt,\. huh?\.\.
\n<\n[3]>That's right.\.\. Ane isn't the only one who would pay for a \ii[22].\.\.
\n<\n[3]>I'm sure with the money from selling it we can find someone who can help get you into the Hole with it without Ane ever knowing.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Hah...\.\.\. \BST[1,Neneko2]You sure you're alright betraying your boss or supplier or whatever?\.\.
n<\n[1]>Not really.\.\. It's your problem,\. anyway.\.\. \BST[8]I just wanna know if this'll get in the way of me getting inside.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Of course.\.\. I suppose I shouldn't be surprised.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Well,\. either way,\. it won't be a problem,\. so back to the matter at hand.\.\. When you're ready to stop wasting time and make a plan,\. let me know.\.\. And hurry it up.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Maybe a little.\.\. We're partners or whatever,\. right?\.\. I have the right to be worried if you're gonna get yourself hunted down or something!\.\.
\n<\n[3]>!!\.\. ...\.\.\. \BST[1]I suppose you have a point.\.\. I admit I am surprised,\. though...\.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>I was not aware you had a heart.\.\. I was beginning to suspect your Mana mutation replaced it with something.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Regardless,\. you don't have to worry about me.\.\. Ane won't be a problem as long as we get you into the Hole.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>We shouldn't dilly dally longer than we need to.\.\. \BST[1]Make sure you're ready for the trip and then we can discuss what to do.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>The Lake Goddess Shrine...\.\.\. I doubt it,\. but are you religious,\. Neneko?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Nah.\.\. I don't need a goddess to do things for me.\.\. \BST[5]I make my own way.\.\. The only girl I rely on is me.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>A rather direct viewpoint...\.\.\. I don't know if that is respectable or not.\.\.

\n<\n[3]>Sigh...\.\.\. either way,\. I suppose you won't have any problem going inside,\. then.\.\. \BST[1]Hopefully your attitude won't anger the goddess and deprive the city and the Hole of its clean water.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Eh?\.\. Is it really that important?\.\. Just looks like a more fancy cave.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>It's a cave that people really care about.\.\. Although most people call that a temple.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>...\.\.\. Although,\. it's not as if people enter it nowadays.\.\. From my understanding,\. there are rumors that at some point it's become infested with monsters.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Given that a Kirin has made it its home,\. I'm inclined to believe those rumors have merit,\. now.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Cave,\. temple,\. monsters,\. whatever.\.\. It's all the same job anyway.\.\. Go in,\. kill the Kirin,\. get out!\.\.
\n<\n[3]>...\.\.\. You think I'm going in there?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>YES,\. you're going in there!\.\. This whole idea was your idea!\.\.
\n<\n[3]>I am a non-\.combatant,\. Neneko.\.\. Did you not hear the part where I said there are monsters?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Are you serious?\.\. You're gonna make me do everything?\.\.
\n<\n[3]>You will do better without me to drag you down,\. I am sure.\.\. ...\.\.\.\BST[8] I wouldn't stand a chance against even the most minor of Melmo.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>I imagine even you would not want a rather quick and messy end to our "partnership".\.\.
\n<\n[3]>To make sure you don't get this wrong,\. clearly!\.\. I will wait here and oversee things.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Hah...\.\.\. whatever.\.\. Rest your pretty butt and short skirt with this statue.\.\. I'm heading in.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Hold it.\.\. Are you sure you have everything you need?\.\.

\n<\n[3]>I mean it,\. Neneko.\.\. There are many contraptions within the temple.\.\. If the Kirin is deeper inside,\. you will need to activate the inner mechanisms of the temple.\.\. Do you know how?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Yeah yeah,\. what do you take me for?\.\. I've scouted this place out already.\.\. Look.\.\.
Neneko pulls out the \ii[13],\. showing it to Kaere.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>...\.\.\. \BST[1]That is correct.\.\. I am surprised.\.\. From what you said before I thought you didn't know about the temple's mechanisms.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>I told ya I make my own way,\. didn't I?!~
\n<\n[3]>Hmm...\.\.\. I suppose you did.\.\. It seems like you've got everything taken care of already.\.\. Perhaps I shouldn't have worried after all.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Damn right you shouldn't have.\.\.\.\.\.\BST[1] Anything else I should worry about in there?\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Not that I'm aware of.\.\. Still,\. it would be best you do not linger for too long,\. in case it turns out there is.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Yeah yeah.\.\. Stay up here and look pretty I guess.\.\. I'll make this quick.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Sigh...\.\.\. You didn't prepare or read up on this place at all,\. did you?\.\.
Kaere rubs her forehead,\. before reaching into her hat and pulling out an item.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Here.\.\. Take this \ii[13].\.\. You will need this to properly explore the temple.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Which one of us is more used to adventuring,\. again?\.\. Were you just expecting to punch the walls and waterfalls after hitting a dead end?\.\.
\n<\n[3]>I suppose it is good that at least one of us has foresight.\.\. Now get going.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Whatever,\. whatever!\.\. Don't get a big head just cause you were useful ONCE on this stupid job you're making me do!\.\.
Kaere's face turns a bit red.\.\. Neneko gets going before she starts nagging again.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Does it look like I am dressed for adventure?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>What,\. never fight a monster in your underwear?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Aren't witches supposed to be cunning and have tricks or something?\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Perhaps you should take that complaint up to the Company blocking us poor commonfolk from studying Mana,\. maybe then I can do a "trick" for you.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Oh,\. it seems that if you do that we would both get arrested or hunted down.\.\. Perhaps you shouldn't,\. then.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Oh.\.\. Are you,\. perhaps,\. scared of getting wet?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>The lake's right there and I'm pretty sure I can pick you up,\. brat.\.\. \BST[1]How about some real advice.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>There's probably some levers inside that can make a path deeper down.\.\. Experiment with them!\.\. Flip anything you see and eventually something must open!\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Ugh,\. how deep is this temple anyway?\.\.
\n<\n[3]>I'm not sure.\.\. No one has bothered entering for a long while.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Uugggggggggh.\.\. How long is this going to take...\.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Longer if you decide to waste time up here.\.\. Now move it!\.\.
\n<\n[1]>You know,\. we'd probably be done faster with two heads exploring the place.\.\.
\n<\n[3]>I am not going past this statue.\.\. And how expansive could this shrine be?\.\. Just cover as much ground as you can and you'll find the Kirin eventually.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>You read that 'advice' out of a beginner guide or what?\.\.
Kaere shoves a small book into her hat,\. hiding it away.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>So you mentioned mechanisms and stuff...\.\.\. anything I should look out for?\.\.
\n<\n[3]>You already have the \ii[13],\. don't you?\.\. Everything should be straightforward once you figure out where to use it.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Did those rumors say anything about what the monsters are like?\.\.
\n<\n[3]>I do not recall.\.\. But I am sure you are capable enough to claw your way to victory.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>How come when you say it it feels like an insult?\.\.
\n<\n[3]>I have the utmost confidence in your tendency towards violence,\. Neneko.\.\.
This scene will be ready in one of the next builds!\.\. Thank you for playing up to this point!
